  "claim_short": "The answer is **no**. There exist separable real Banach spaces (E,F) and closed, proper, generating cones (E_+,F_+) for which the closed completed projective cone in (E\\widehat\\otimes_\\pi F) contains a nonzero linear subspace. It is therefore not proper and cannot be contained in any proper cone.",
